{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":840,"text":"All right, I want to see a show of hands:"},{"time":2817,"text":"how many of you have\nunfriended someone on Facebook"},{"time":5240,"text":"because they said something offensive\nabout politics or religion,"},{"time":9120,"text":"childcare, food?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13240,"text":"And how many of you\nknow at least one person that you avoid"},{"time":16079,"text":"because you just don't want\nto talk to them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20960,"text":"You know, it used to be that in order\nto have a polite conversation,"},{"time":24200,"text":"we just had to follow the advice\nof Henry Higgins in \"My Fair Lady\":"},{"time":27440,"text":"Stick to the weather and your health."},{"time":29280,"text":"But these days, with climate change\nand anti-vaxxing, those subjects --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"are not safe either."},{"time":35320,"text":"So this world that we live in,"},{"time":38520,"text":"this world in which every conversation"},{"time":41120,"text":"has the potential\nto devolve into an argument,"},{"time":43320,"text":"where our politicians\ncan't speak to one another"},{"time":45630,"text":"and where even the most trivial of issues"},{"time":47960,"text":"have someone fighting both passionately\nfor it and against it, it's not normal."},{"time":52960,"text":"Pew Research did a study\nof 10,000 American adults,"},{"time":56080,"text":"and they found that at this moment,\nwe are more polarized,"},{"time":58840,"text":"we are more divided,"},{"time":60160,"text":"than we ever have been in history."},{"time":62960,"text":"We're less likely to compromise,"},{"time":64560,"text":"which means we're\nnot listening to each other."},{"time":66760,"text":"And we make decisions about where to live,"},{"time":69320,"text":"who to marry and even\nwho our friends are going to be,"},{"time":71960,"text":"based on what we already believe."},{"time":74080,"text":"Again, that means\nwe're not listening to each other."},{"time":77080,"text":"A conversation requires a balance\nbetween talking and listening,"},{"time":80440,"text":"and somewhere along the way,\nwe lost that balance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83120,"text":"Now, part of that is due to technology."},{"time":85040,"text":"The smartphones that you all\neither have in your hands"},{"time":87640,"text":"or close enough that you could\ngrab them really quickly."},{"time":90320,"text":"According to Pew Research,"},{"time":91640,"text":"about a third of American teenagers\nsend more than a hundred texts a day."},{"time":96560,"text":"And many of them, almost most of them,\nare more likely to text their friends"},{"time":101160,"text":"than they are to talk\nto them face to face."},{"time":104160,"text":"There's this great piece in The Atlantic."},{"time":106160,"text":"It was written by a high school teacher\nnamed Paul Barnwell."},{"time":109040,"text":"And he gave his kids\na communication project."},{"time":111200,"text":"He wanted to teach them how to speak\non a specific subject without using notes."},{"time":114960,"text":"And he said this: \"I came to realize...\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":116889,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120200,"text":"\"I came to realize\nthat conversational competence"},{"time":123400,"text":"might be the single\nmost overlooked skill we fail to teach."},{"time":127520,"text":"Kids spend hours each day engaging\nwith ideas and each other through screens,"},{"time":131840,"text":"but rarely do they have an opportunity"},{"time":133720,"text":"to hone their interpersonal\ncommunications skills."},{"time":136320,"text":"It might sound like a funny question,\nbut we have to ask ourselves:"},{"time":139520,"text":"Is there any 21st-century skill"},{"time":141480,"text":"more important than being able to sustain\ncoherent, confident conversation?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":147080,"text":"Now, I make my living talking to people:"},{"time":149320,"text":"Nobel Prize winners, truck drivers,"},{"time":151600,"text":"billionaires, kindergarten teachers,"},{"time":154040,"text":"heads of state, plumbers."},{"time":156760,"text":"I talk to people that I like.\nI talk to people that I don't like."},{"time":159832,"text":"I talk to some people that I disagree with\ndeeply on a personal level."},{"time":163640,"text":"But I still have\na great conversation with them."},{"time":166440,"text":"So I'd like to spend the next 10 minutes\nor so teaching you how to talk"},{"time":170360,"text":"and how to listen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172800,"text":"Many of you have already heard\na lot of advice on this,"},{"time":175440,"text":"things like look the person in the eye,"},{"time":177440,"text":"think of interesting topics\nto discuss in advance,"},{"time":181280,"text":"look, nod and smile to show\nthat you're paying attention,"},{"time":186080,"text":"repeat back what you just heard\nor summarize it."},{"time":189000,"text":"So I want you to forget all of that."},{"time":190760,"text":"It is crap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":195040,"text":"There is no reason to learn\nhow to show you're paying attention"},{"time":199320,"text":"if you are in fact paying attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204880,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207800,"text":"Now, I actually use the exact\nsame skills as a professional interviewer"},{"time":211480,"text":"that I do in regular life."},{"time":214440,"text":"So, I'm going to teach you\nhow to interview people,"},{"time":217920,"text":"and that's actually going to help you\nlearn how to be better conversationalists."},{"time":221760,"text":"Learn to have a conversation"},{"time":223160,"text":"without wasting your time,\nwithout getting bored,"},{"time":225520,"text":"and, please God,\nwithout offending anybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228840,"text":"We've all had really great conversations."},{"time":231080,"text":"We've had them before.\nWe know what it's like."},{"time":233280,"text":"The kind of conversation where you\nwalk away feeling engaged and inspired,"},{"time":237000,"text":"or where you feel\nlike you've made a real connection"},{"time":239480,"text":"or you've been perfectly understood."},{"time":241600,"text":"There is no reason"},{"time":242840,"text":"why most of your interactions\ncan't be like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246120,"text":"So I have 10 basic rules.\nI'm going to walk you through all of them,"},{"time":249360,"text":"but honestly, if you just choose\none of them and master it,"},{"time":253120,"text":"you'll already enjoy better conversations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255880,"text":"Number one: Don't multitask."},{"time":258120,"text":"And I don't mean\njust set down your cell phone"},{"time":260320,"text":"or your tablet or your car keys\nor whatever is in your hand."},{"time":263200,"text":"I mean, be present."},{"time":265120,"text":"Be in that moment."},{"time":267400,"text":"Don't think about your argument\nyou had with your boss."},{"time":270040,"text":"Don't think about what\nyou're going to have for dinner."},{"time":272680,"text":"If you want to get out\nof the conversation,"},{"time":274760,"text":"get out of the conversation,"},{"time":276160,"text":"but don't be half in it\nand half out of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278320,"text":"Number two: Don't pontificate."},{"time":280920,"text":"If you want to state your opinion"},{"time":283120,"text":"without any opportunity for response\nor argument or pushback or growth,"},{"time":289080,"text":"write a blog."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293640,"text":"Now, there's a really good reason\nwhy I don't allow pundits on my show:"},{"time":297040,"text":"Because they're really boring."},{"time":298840,"text":"If they're conservative, they're going to\nhate Obama and food stamps and abortion."},{"time":302722,"text":"If they're liberal, they're going to hate"},{"time":304720,"text":"big banks and oil corporations\nand Dick Cheney."},{"time":306960,"text":"Totally predictable."},{"time":308240,"text":"And you don't want to be like that."},{"time":309960,"text":"You need to enter every conversation\nassuming that you have something to learn."},{"time":315520,"text":"The famed therapist M. Scott Peck said"},{"time":317680,"text":"that true listening requires\na setting aside of oneself."},{"time":322120,"text":"And sometimes that means\nsetting aside your personal opinion."},{"time":326200,"text":"He said that sensing this acceptance,"},{"time":329520,"text":"the speaker will become\nless and less vulnerable"},{"time":331800,"text":"and more and more likely\nto open up the inner recesses"},{"time":334680,"text":"of his or her mind to the listener."},{"time":337360,"text":"Again, assume that you have\nsomething to learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340880,"text":"Bill Nye: \"Everyone you will ever meet\nknows something that you don't.\""},{"time":345240,"text":"I put it this way:"},{"time":346600,"text":"Everybody is an expert in something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351160,"text":"Number three: Use open-ended questions."},{"time":354000,"text":"In this case, take a cue from journalists."},{"time":356080,"text":"Start your questions with who,\nwhat, when, where, why or how."},{"time":359200,"text":"If you put in a complicated question,\nyou're going to get a simple answer out."},{"time":362920,"text":"If I ask you, \"Were you terrified?\""},{"time":365280,"text":"you're going to respond to the most\npowerful word in that sentence,"},{"time":368480,"text":"which is \"terrified,\" and the answer is\n\"Yes, I was\" or \"No, I wasn't.\""},{"time":371840,"text":"\"Were you angry?\" \"Yes, I was very angry.\""},{"time":373864,"text":"Let them describe it.\nThey're the ones that know."},{"time":376960,"text":"Try asking them things like,\n\"What was that like?\""},{"time":379960,"text":"\"How did that feel?\""},{"time":381440,"text":"Because then they might have to stop\nfor a moment and think about it,"},{"time":385760,"text":"and you're going to get\na much more interesting response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388760,"text":"Number four: Go with the flow."},{"time":391720,"text":"That means thoughts\nwill come into your mind"},{"time":394560,"text":"and you need to let them\ngo out of your mind."},{"time":397640,"text":"We've heard interviews often"},{"time":399640,"text":"in which a guest is talking\nfor several minutes"},{"time":402120,"text":"and then the host comes back in\nand asks a question"},{"time":404560,"text":"which seems like it comes out of nowhere,\nor it's already been answered."},{"time":408000,"text":"That means the host probably\nstopped listening two minutes ago"},{"time":410960,"text":"because he thought\nof this really clever question,"},{"time":414400,"text":"and he was just bound\nand determined to say that."},{"time":417440,"text":"And we do the exact same thing."},{"time":419440,"text":"We're sitting there having\na conversation with someone,"},{"time":422080,"text":"and then we remember that time\nthat we met Hugh Jackman in a coffee shop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":426920,"text":"And we stop listening."},{"time":428560,"text":"Stories and ideas\nare going to come to you."},{"time":430640,"text":"You need to let them come and let them go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434080,"text":"Number five: If you don't know,\nsay that you don't know."},{"time":438800,"text":"Now, people on the radio,\nespecially on NPR,"},{"time":441120,"text":"are much more aware\nthat they're going on the record,"},{"time":444080,"text":"and so they're more careful\nabout what they claim to be an expert in"},{"time":447680,"text":"and what they claim to know for sure."},{"time":449840,"text":"Do that. Err on the side of caution."},{"time":452240,"text":"Talk should not be cheap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454640,"text":"Number six: Don't equate\nyour experience with theirs."},{"time":459280,"text":"If they're talking\nabout having lost a family member,"},{"time":462080,"text":"don't start talking about the time\nyou lost a family member."},{"time":464960,"text":"If they're talking about the trouble\nthey're having at work,"},{"time":467840,"text":"don't tell them about\nhow much you hate your job."},{"time":470200,"text":"It's not the same. It is never the same."},{"time":472160,"text":"All experiences are individual."},{"time":473960,"text":"And, more importantly,\nit is not about you."},{"time":477120,"text":"You don't need to take that moment\nto prove how amazing you are"},{"time":481040,"text":"or how much you've suffered."},{"time":483120,"text":"Somebody asked Stephen Hawking once\nwhat his IQ was, and he said,"},{"time":486200,"text":"\"I have no idea. People who brag\nabout their IQs are losers.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":489120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":491080,"text":"Conversations are not\na promotional opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496560,"text":"Number seven:"},{"time":499440,"text":"Try not to repeat yourself."},{"time":500840,"text":"It's condescending,\nand it's really boring,"},{"time":503240,"text":"and we tend to do it a lot."},{"time":504920,"text":"Especially in work conversations\nor in conversations with our kids,"},{"time":508880,"text":"we have a point to make,"},{"time":510160,"text":"so we just keep rephrasing it\nover and over."},{"time":513640,"text":"Don't do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514880,"text":"Number eight: Stay out of the weeds."},{"time":517200,"text":"Frankly, people don't care"},{"time":520039,"text":"about the years, the names,"},{"time":522679,"text":"the dates, all those details"},{"time":524640,"text":"that you're struggling\nto come up with in your mind."},{"time":527120,"text":"They don't care.\nWhat they care about is you."},{"time":529880,"text":"They care about what you're like,"},{"time":532080,"text":"what you have in common."},{"time":533800,"text":"So forget the details. Leave them out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536880,"text":"Number nine:"},{"time":538120,"text":"This is not the last one,\nbut it is the most important one."},{"time":541400,"text":"Listen."},{"time":542960,"text":"I cannot tell you how many\nreally important people have said"},{"time":546400,"text":"that listening is perhaps the most,\nthe number one most important skill"},{"time":550320,"text":"that you could develop."},{"time":551560,"text":"Buddha said, and I'm paraphrasing,"},{"time":553480,"text":"\"If your mouth is open,\nyou're not learning.\""},{"time":556040,"text":"And Calvin Coolidge said, \"No man\never listened his way out of a job.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":560680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":562160,"text":"Why do we not listen to each other?"},{"time":564920,"text":"Number one, we'd rather talk."},{"time":567480,"text":"When I'm talking, I'm in control."},{"time":569320,"text":"I don't have to hear anything\nI'm not interested in."},{"time":571800,"text":"I'm the center of attention."},{"time":573200,"text":"I can bolster my own identity."},{"time":575120,"text":"But there's another reason:"},{"time":576520,"text":"We get distracted."},{"time":578000,"text":"The average person talks\nat about 225 word per minute,"},{"time":581560,"text":"but we can listen at up to\n500 words per minute."},{"time":585880,"text":"So our minds are filling in\nthose other 275 words."},{"time":589880,"text":"And look, I know,\nit takes effort and energy"},{"time":593080,"text":"to actually pay attention to someone,"},{"time":595400,"text":"but if you can't do that,\nyou're not in a conversation."},{"time":598400,"text":"You're just two people shouting out\nbarely related sentences"},{"time":601280,"text":"in the same place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":604480,"text":"You have to listen to one another."},{"time":607000,"text":"Stephen Covey said it very beautifully."},{"time":608920,"text":"He said, \"Most of us don't listen\nwith the intent to understand."},{"time":612880,"text":"We listen with the intent to reply.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":616960,"text":"One more rule, number 10,\nand it's this one: Be brief."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620840,"text":"[A good conversation is like a miniskirt;\nshort enough to retain interest,"},{"time":624360,"text":"but long enough to cover\nthe subject. -- My Sister]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":626800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628040,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":630480,"text":"All of this boils down to the same\nbasic concept, and it is this one:"},{"time":635320,"text":"Be interested in other people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638200,"text":"You know, I grew up\nwith a very famous grandfather,"},{"time":640640,"text":"and there was kind of a ritual in my home."},{"time":642720,"text":"People would come over\nto talk to my grandparents,"},{"time":645200,"text":"and after they would leave,\nmy mother would come over to us,"},{"time":648080,"text":"and she'd say, \"Do you know who that was?"},{"time":650080,"text":"She was the runner-up to Miss America."},{"time":651960,"text":"He was the mayor of Sacramento."},{"time":653680,"text":"She won a Pulitzer Prize.\nHe's a Russian ballet dancer.\""},{"time":656880,"text":"And I kind of grew up assuming"},{"time":660280,"text":"everyone has some hidden,\namazing thing about them."},{"time":663680,"text":"And honestly, I think\nit's what makes me a better host."},{"time":667280,"text":"I keep my mouth shut\nas often as I possibly can,"},{"time":670120,"text":"I keep my mind open,"},{"time":671560,"text":"and I'm always prepared to be amazed,"},{"time":674080,"text":"and I'm never disappointed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676760,"text":"You do the same thing."},{"time":678640,"text":"Go out, talk to people,"},{"time":681080,"text":"listen to people,"},{"time":682320,"text":"and, most importantly,\nbe prepared to be amazed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686440,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687680,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}